<p>Expo Application Services involves building and distributing your application code, not your application data. Thus, Expo is not aware of your users&#x27; identities and does not store or handle PII related to your users. If you use the Expo push notification service to distribute push notifications, Expo will store the push tokens required to send notifications to your users and will delete the push notification payload after it has been sent to Google FCM or Apple APNs. EAS Update uses randomly generated device install IDs to determine which devices have requested an update. You can read more about the data we collect and how we handle it in our <a class="text-link transition-opacity hocus:opacity-80" href="/privacy-explained">Privacy Explained document</a>.</p>
<p>In all scenarios regarding our users&#x27; data, Expo is GDPR-, CCPA-, and Data Privacy Framework-compliant.</p>
